A simple jenkins pipeline to verify if the docker slave configuration is working as expected.

ðŸš€ Jenkins Pipeline with Docker: Node.js Version Test


ðŸ“‹ What This Pipeline Does
âœ… Uses Docker to create a lightweight container running Node.js version 16 (alpine edition).

âœ… Runs a simple shell command to print the installed Node.js version.

âœ… Helps verify that the Docker image and Node.js environment are working correctly.


ðŸ§± Pipeline Breakdown
ðŸ”¹ agent { docker { image 'node:16-alpine' } }
This tells Jenkins to spin up a Docker container using the official Node.js v16 (Alpine) image to run the steps inside the pipeline.

ðŸ”¹ stage('Test')
A stage is a section in the pipeline. In this case, it's named "Test" and is used to perform a single task.

ðŸ”¹ sh 'node --version'
Runs the shell command node --version inside the container, which prints out the installed Node.js version Example,

v16.20.0.
